Full Title: Conference on Bilingual Acquisition in Early Childhood 
Short Title: BAEC 2008 

Date: 11-Dec-2008 - 12-Dec-2008
Location: The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Hong Kong 
Contact Person: Angel Chan
Meeting Email: cbrc@cuhk.edu.hk
Web Site: http://www.cuhk.edu.hk/lin/conference/baec/ 

Linguistic Field(s): Language Acquisition; Psycholinguistics 

Call Deadline: 15-Jun-2008 

Meeting Description:

An international conference on Bilingual Acquisition in Early Childhood will be held at the Chinese University of Hong Kong (CUHK) from 11-12 December 2008. The conference is organized by the newly established Childhood Bilingualism Research Centre at the Chinese University of Hong Kong & Co-sponsored by the Linguistic Society of Hong Kong.

Keynote Speakers:
Brian MacWhinney (Carnegie Mellon University) 
William O'Grady (University of Hawai'i) 
Johanne Paradis (University of Alberta) 
Yasuhiro Shirai (University of Pittsburgh) 

Call for Papers

We invite proposals for paper presentations on relevant topics including (but not restricted to) the following: 
- Bilingual acquisition of East Asian languages
- Bilingual acquisition in special populations
- Bilingual first language acquisition
- Child second language acquisition
- Cross-linguistic influence in bilingual development
- Input studies in bilingual acquisition

Please visit: http://www.cuhk.edu.hk/lin/conference/baec/ for details.

Deadline for submission of abstract: June 15, 2008
 




